verbose_text: FIXa and FXa are inhibited by AT which binds to the active sites located on the heavy chain of these trypsin like serine proteases, and FXa is inhibited by the Kunitz domain 2 of TFPI interacting with the serine protease domain located on the heavy chain of FXa.
evidence: FXa is inhibited by the Kunitz domain 2 of TFPI interacting with the serine protease
